#: ../../../guides/recipes/continuous-integration-github-actions.md:0
msgid "Continuous Integration with GitHub Actions and a binary cache"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/continuous-integration-github-actions.md:0
msgid "CI, Continuous Integration, GitHub Actions, Binary Cache, Nix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/continuous-integration-github-actions.md:10
msgid "Continuous integration with GitHub Actions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/continuous-integration-github-actions.md:12
msgid ""
"In this guide, we'll show you **a few short steps** to get started using "
"[GitHub Actions](https://github.com/features/actions) as your continuous "
"integration (CI) workflow for commits and pull requests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/continuous-integration-github-actions.md:14
msgid ""
"One benefit of Nix is that **CI can build and cache developer environments "
"for every project** on every branch using binary caches."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/continuous-integration-github-actions.md:16
msgid ""
"An important aspect of CI is the feedback loop of, **how many minutes does "
"the build take to finish?**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/continuous-integration-github-actions.md:18
msgid ""
"There are several good options, but Cachix (below) is the most "
"straightforward."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/continuous-integration-github-actions.md:20
msgid "Caching builds using Cachix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/continuous-integration-github-actions.md:22
msgid ""
"Using [Cachix](https://cachix.org/) you'll never have to waste time building "
"a derivation twice, and you'll share built derivations with all your "
"developers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/continuous-integration-github-actions.md:24
msgid "After each job, just-built derivations are pushed to your binary cache."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/continuous-integration-github-actions.md:26
msgid ""
"Before each job, derivations to be built are first substituted (if they "
"exist) from your binary cache."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/continuous-integration-github-actions.md:28
msgid "1. Creating your first binary cache"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/continuous-integration-github-actions.md:30
msgid ""
"It's recommended to have different binary caches per team, depending on who "
"will have write/read access to it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/continuous-integration-github-actions.md:32
msgid ""
"Fill out the form on the [create binary cache](https://app.cachix.org/cache) "
"page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/continuous-integration-github-actions.md:34
msgid ""
"On your freshly created binary cache, follow the **Push binaries** tab "
"instructions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/continuous-integration-github-actions.md:36
msgid "2. Setting up secrets"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/continuous-integration-github-actions.md:38
msgid ""
"On your GitHub repository or organization (for use across all repositories):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/continuous-integration-github-actions.md:40
msgid "Click on `Settings`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/continuous-integration-github-actions.md:41
msgid "Click on `Secrets`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/continuous-integration-github-actions.md:42
msgid ""
"Add your previously generated secrets (`CACHIX_SIGNING_KEY` and/or "
"`CACHIX_AUTH_TOKEN`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/continuous-integration-github-actions.md:44
msgid "3. Setting up GitHub Actions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/continuous-integration-github-actions.md:46
msgid "Create `.github/workflows/test.yml` with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/continuous-integration-github-actions.md:48
msgid ""
"name: \"Test\"\n"
"on:\n"
"  pull_request:\n"
"  push:\n"
"jobs:\n"
"  tests:\n"
"    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n"
"    steps:\n"
"    - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n"
"    - uses: cachix/install-nix-action@v25\n"
"      with:\n"
"        nix_path: nixpkgs=channel:nixos-unstable\n"
"    - uses: cachix/cachix-action@v14\n"
"      with:\n"
"        name: mycache\n"
"        # If you chose signing key for write access\n"
"        signingKey: '${{ secrets.CACHIX_SIGNING_KEY }}'\n"
"        # If you chose API tokens for write access OR if you have a private "
"cache\n"
"        authToken: '${{ secrets.CACHIX_AUTH_TOKEN }}'\n"
"    - run: nix-build\n"
"    - run: nix-shell --run \"echo OK\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/continuous-integration-github-actions.md:72
msgid ""
"Once you commit and push to your GitHub repository, you should see status "
"checks appearing on commits and PRs."
msgstr ""

